 little dent.

… You reload to the bottom the barrel,

With a creaking of springs

Resiliently pressing it down on the floor,

And you see, half concealed by the door,

That your double has stopped in the mirror,

Rainbow feathers in head band

Standing on end.



The author had occasion to hide (we are now in the Godunov-Cherdyntsevs’ mansion on the English Quay of the Neva, where it stands even today) among draperies, under tables, behind the upright cushions of silk divans, in a wardrobe,